### Scope Contract 5: Full Acceptance Checklist — [HUMAN STEP]

**⚠ This scope is executed by the human. No code changes.**

Run every item below on the live `https://munrhalls.com` domain. Check each item as verified.

**Layout & Responsiveness**
- [ ] Desktop (≥ 1024px): homepage 3×3 grid, canvas centered, 4 zones in corners
- [ ] Mobile (< 640px): homepage canvas at top, zones stacked in order (About, Sanglogium, Contact, Skills)
- [ ] Desktop: case study 2-column alternating layout + sticky nav
- [ ] Mobile: case study single column

**Canvas**
- [ ] Canvas animates at 60fps (DevTools Performance → FPS meter ≥ 55)
- [ ] CJK ring rotates counter-clockwise
- [ ] Matrix rain falls top-to-bottom inside inner diamond
- [ ] OS `prefers-reduced-motion` ON → canvas shows static frame (two diamond outlines, no animation)
- [ ] Switch tabs → animation pauses (verified via DevTools Performance CPU)
- [ ] Navigate homepage → away → back → no duplicate animation loops

**Case Study**
- [ ] All 14 sections visible; sticky nav appears after hero scrolls past
- [ ] Active section pill highlighted correctly while scrolling
- [ ] Mobile: horizontal pill row scrollable; active pill auto-scrolls into view
- [ ] Section titles fully visible below sticky nav after clicking pills (scroll-margin-top working)
- [ ] Navigate case study → away → back → IntersectionObservers do not stack

**Accessibility & Keyboard**
- [ ] Keyboard Tab: all 4 HomeBlock zones reachable, focus rings visible
- [ ] Keyboard Tab: sticky nav pills reachable on case study page
- [ ] Skip link visible on first Tab press on case study page
- [ ] `aria-current="true"` on active nav pill (DevTools Accessibility tree)

**Contact Form**
- [ ] Form submits successfully (verify in Formspree dashboard)
- [ ] Honeypot field hidden in DOM; filling it silently blocks submission
- [ ] Navigate away after submit → back → form resets to fresh state
- [ ] Error state shows `mailto:` fallback link when Formspree is blocked

**Content & Links**
- [ ] Resume PDF downloads (`/resume.pdf`)
- [ ] All 4 nav links resolve (no 404)
- [ ] LinkedIn and GitHub links open correct pages in new tab
- [ ] No 404s anywhere (check DevTools Network for red requests)

## Simplicity Guardrails

- Is build the simplest possible? (Yes: single `astro build` command)
- Is deploy the simplest possible? (Yes: static file upload via hosting panel — no CI/CD pipeline)
- Are acceptance checks the simplest possible? (Yes: manual browser verification + Lighthouse, no automated test suite)
